<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2331] Rolling file appender concatenating debug message instead of using formatting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2331</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When debug is on, RollingFileAppender prints the&#160;shutdown message and concatenates the name, instead of passing it as an argument to be formatted:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`&quot;Shutting down RollingFileManager {}&quot; + getName()`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`&quot;Shutting down RollingFileManager {}&quot;, getName()`&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Any - Mac with log4j 2.11.0 using `-Dlog4j.debug` and a RollingFileAppender&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
